  "text": "It was observed that for both DTI and ST α\" did not have a simple circumferential pattern, but rather had high negative values in the anterio-lateral myocardium (blue in Figure 6C and Figure 13 ). This pattern closely follows that reported for normal rat heart DTI in the literature [CITATION_1] . It is likely largely a result of the cylindrical coordinate system used, which is based on a centroid optimized on the whole heart, rather than an individual slice and is a known source of error in α\" [CITATION_2] , but it may to some degree be due to true variation of α\".",
